Valley Protective Services<br>
<br>
Here at Valley Protective Services we are driven by an uncompromising dedication to professionalism and an enduring commitment to place principle before profit. We are currently looking for security officers to post at locations in Albuquerque, and Sante Fe. Must at least have a level 1 guard license.<br>
<br>
Pay Scale: Starting between $10 and $12 an hour<br>
<br>
Some Job Descriptions:<br>
<br>
Patrol communities talking to people to verify residency and status for being on property and noting all in a nightly report for the client.<br>
<br>
Looking for safety and maintenance issues on property to note for the client.<br>
<br>
Handling noise complaints, and other issues that may arise.<br>
<br>
Valley Protective Services. Private Investigations Advisory Board License #2158<br>
<br>
Skills / Requirements<br>
1. Must be 18yrs or older.<br>
2. Have no felony convictions ever.<br>
3. Have no misdemeanor convictions in the last 5 years.<br>
4. Have good communication skills, spoken and written.<br>
5. You must be a citizen or legal resident who is authorized to seek employment in the United States.<br>
6. Must have a valid NM Driver's License and a reliable car or truck with automobile insurance<br>
7. Must be High School Graduate or equivalent (GED) (Must show proof)<br>
8. Must be available to work nights, weekends, and holidays.<br>
9. Must have at least a level one guard license.<br>
<br>
Come visit us at 3916 Carlisle Blvd. NE Ste. D Albuquerque, NM 87107<br>
Monday interviews are open interviews or by appointment from 9:00am to 5:00pm, Tuesday through Saturday interviews are by appointment only. Please submit resume with all contact information for fastest response to set up appointment for interview. <br>
<br>
Please dress appropriately for the interview, bring your drivers license and resume.    </section>

